'''Cemuhî''' (Camuhi, Camuki, Tyamuhi, Wagap) is an [[Oceanic languages|Oceanic]] language spoken on the island of [[New Caledonia]], in the area of [[Poindimié]], [[Koné, New Caledonia|Koné]], and [[Touho]]. The language has approximately 3,300 speakers and is considered a regional language of France.

==Phonology==
===Consonants===
Cèmuhî has a consonantal distinction of what Rivierre (1980) calls nasal, semi-nasal, and oral consonants. He refers to voiced oral consonants as semi-nasal because they are always prenasalized. <ref>Rivierre ([[#grammar|1980]]).</ref>

