{{Infobox language |name = Sapo |states = [[Liberia]] |speakers = {{sigfig|36400|2}} |date=2006 |ref=e18 |familycolor = Niger-Congo |fam2 = [[Atlantic–Congo languages|Atlantic–Congo]] |fam3 = [[Kru languages|Kru]] |fam4 = [[Western Kru languages|Western Kru]] |fam5 = [[Wee languages|Wee]] |fam6 = Guere–Krahn |iso3 = krn |glotto=sapo1251 |glottorefname=Sapo }}
The '''Sapo language''', also known as '''Sarpo''' or '''Southern Krahn''', is a [[Kru languages|Kru]] language of the [[Niger–Congo languages|Niger–Congo]] [[language family]]. It is spoken in eastern [[Liberia]], primarily in [[Grand Gedeh County]] and [[Sinoe County]], by the [[Sapo people]]. Its dialects include: Juarzon, Kabade (Karbardae), Nomopo (Nimpo), Putu, Sinkon (Senkon), and Waya (Wedjah).
